    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You could write a transform to pick up these require statements in the same way that browserify or brfs does, replacing the values with inlined assets (or URLs). If you wanted to store the assets in a user-specified location, you could pass that directory to the transform using [subarg](https://github.com/substack/subarg) syntax, e.g.:\n\n``` bash\nbrowserify index.js -o bundle.js -t [ image-emitter -d ./static/ ]\n```\n\nI've also been considering writing a transform that picks up calls to `insert-css` or another package – removing them from the JavaScript bundle and combining them into a single specified file, e.g.:\n\n``` javascript\nrequire('insert-css')(require('fs').readFileSync(__dirname + '/style.css', 'utf8'))\nrequire('concat-css')('./style.css')\n```\n\n``` bash\nbrowserify index.js -o bundle.js -g [ concat-css bundle.css ]\n```\n",
