    "body": "Here's what I've got so far. [urify](https://www.npmjs.org/package/urify) allows you to inline `datauri` calls into your bundle. This means modules could start inlining images/etc right now and the code would run in node and browserify. \n\nThe next step is to \"emit\" the files of all your dependencies at a top-level application directory, using a browserify plugin. For this you can use [urify-emitter](https://www.npmjs.org/package/urify-emitter).\n\nThe problem I'm running into now is that the urify-transformed module dependencies are already transformed by the time they reach the urify-emitter transform. So only the top-level assets would be emitted.\n\nWhat is needed is like global-transforms, but \"override transforms.\" So that it actually overrides the transform behaviour for all node_modules.\n",
